<p>Minneapolis's cold climate demands robust HVAC systems capable of maintaining comfort during harsh winters while remaining efficient during humid summers. For heating, cold-climate heat pumps have become increasingly popular, with modern units operating effectively down to -13¬∞F and serving as backup systems to temperatures as low as -25¬∞F. These systems typically achieve HSPF ratings of 10+ and can provide both heating and cooling with SEER ratings of 16-20, making them ideal for year-round comfort.</p>

